## Final Quality Checklist

Before finalizing, verify:

- Existing roadmap epics and newly proposed initiatives were evaluated under the same criteria.
- The selected initiative is not chosen merely because it appears first in the roadmap.
- The recommendation is grounded in the projection and roadmap completion context.
- The roadmap was treated as advisory, not authoritative.
- Hidden dependencies and intermediary initiatives were considered.
- Existential or systemic risks were considered before ordinary feature progress.
- Drift signals were considered.
- Established commitments and invariants were respected.
- No roadmap modification was performed.
- No selected epic was rewritten.
- No codebase audit was performed.
- No implementation plan was produced.
- If no safe epic exists, Roadmap Revision Required or Strategic Investigation Required was selected.
